From: "wuyi.shen" <wuyi.shen@cixtech.com>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 10:33:26 +0800
Subject: DPTSW-25537: drm/cix/dptx: HPD fast replug link train (stream-keep)

Re-train DP link on hotplug insert using the last atomic-committed mode
when userspace keeps the display pipeline enabled (fast replug). Use a
stream-keep path (core_off/core_on + video stream) so Wayland does not
need a new encoder_enable to light the panel.

Clear last_mode after encoder_disable/unprepare so slow replug skips plug
train and avoids racing with mutter enable. Only run plug train when
DPTX_STATE_ENABLED and active_stream_cnt are set.

Also fix core_on(shallow) to skip SOURCE_ENABLE via train_done, and use
core_on(false) in prepare for boot source enable.

hpd_plug_link_train defaults to Y (module param; set 0 to disable)

Signed-off-by: wuyi.shen <wuyi.shen@cixtech.com>
Change-Id: If18ddf64f6c465638f54e3167529b626165f2989
Signed-off-by: wuyi.shen <wuyi.shen@cixtech.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.c | 162 +++++++++-
 drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_dptx.h |  10 +
 drivers/gpu/drm/cix/dptx/trilin_drm.c  |  10 +
 3 files changed, 181 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

